# Language Conventions

## Chat (Chinese)

- Internal reasoning and all user-facing replies must be in **Chinese**
- Explanations, summaries, commit messages suggested in chat, and PR descriptions in chat: **Chinese**
- Technical terms may stay in English when natural (e.g. React, CMake, WebSocket)

## Code (English only)

All project source code must use **English only**. Do not use Chinese anywhere in code:

- Identifiers: variables, functions, classes, types, enums, constants
- Comments and docstrings
- String literals shown in UI or logs (unless i18n is explicitly requested)
- Error messages, log messages, assertion text
- Commit messages and PR bodies when written into the repo (English)

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const 用户列表 = []; // 获取所有用户
throw new Error('连接失败');

// ✅ GOOD
const userList = []; // Fetch all users
throw new Error('Connection failed');
```

```cpp
// ❌ BAD
// 初始化 WebSocket 服务
void 启动服务器();

// ✅ GOOD
// Initialize WebSocket service
void startServer();
```

## Exceptions

- User explicitly asks for Chinese in code or UI copy
- Existing Chinese in legacy code: do not expand it; prefer English when touching that area
- `.mdc` rule files and user-facing docs under `docs/` may use Chinese for prose; code blocks inside them still follow English-only for code
